    "anchor": "references",
    "sectionNumber": "10",
    "category": "References",
    "title": "FAA Pilot References",
    "contentHtml": "<h4>Core Regulations (14 CFR)</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Part 1 — Definitions and abbreviations</li>\n      <li>Part 61 — Certification: Pilots, flight instructors, and ground instructors</li>\n      <li>Part 67 — Medical standards and certification</li>\n      <li>Part 71 — Designation of airspace</li>\n      <li>Part 73 — Special use airspace</li>\n      <li>Part 91 — General operating and flight rules</li>\n      <li>Part 97 — Standard instrument procedures</li>\n      <li>Part 107 — Small UAS</li>\n      <li>Part 141 — Pilot schools</li>\n      <li>Part 43 — Maintenance, preventive maintenance, rebuilding, and alteration (incl. Appx A(c) preventive maintenance)</li>\n      <li>NTSB 49 CFR Part 830 — Notification and reporting of aircraft accidents/incidents.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>Aeronautical Information</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>AIM — Aeronautical Information Manual</li>\n      <li>Chart User's Guide — FAA Aeronautical Chart User's Guide</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>FAA Handbooks (FAA-H series)</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-25 — Pilot's Handbook of Aeronautical Knowledge (PHAK)</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-3 — Airplane Flying Handbook (AFH)</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-2 — Risk Management Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-1 — Aircraft Weight and Balance Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-9 — Aviation Instructor's Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-15 — Instrument Flying Handbook (IFH)</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-16 — Instrument Procedures Handbook (IPH)</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-28 — Aviation Weather Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-21 — Helicopter Flying Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-13 — Glider Flying Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-11 — Balloon Flying Handbook</li>\n      <li>FAA-H-8083-23 — Seaplane, Skiplane, and Float/Ski-Equipped Aircraft Operations</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>Airman Certification Standards (ACS)</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>FAA-S-ACS-6 — Private Pilot Airplane</li>\n      <li>FAA-S-ACS-7 — Commercial Pilot Airplane</li>\n      <li>FAA-S-ACS-8 — Instrument Rating Airplane</li>\n      <li>FAA-S-ACS-11 — Airline Transport Pilot and Type Rating (Airplane)</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>Key Advisory Circulars (AC)</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>AC 00-6 — Aviation Weather</li>\n      <li>AC 00-45 — Aviation Weather Services</li>\n      <li>AC 60-22 — Aeronautical Decision Making</li>\n      <li>AC 61-65 — Certification: Pilots and Flight/Ground Instructors (endorsements)</li>\n      <li>AC 61-98 — Currency, Flight Review, and proficiency guidance</li>\n      <li>AC 68-1 — BasicMed</li>\n      <li>AC 90-23 — Aircraft Wake Turbulence</li>\n      <li>AC 90-48 — Pilots' Role in Collision Avoidance</li>\n      <li>AC 90-66 — Non-Towered Airport Flight Operations</li>\n      <li>AC 91-73 — Part 91/135 Surface Movement Guidance</li>\n      <li>AC 91-74 — Pilot Guide: Flight in Icing Conditions</li>\n      <li>AC 91-92 — Pilot's Guide to a Preflight Briefing</li>\n      <li>AC 120-76 — Authorization for Use of Electronic Flight Bags (EFB)</li>\n    </ul>\n    <h4>ATC/Procedural Orders (for reference)</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>FAA JO 7110.65 — Air Traffic Control</li>\n      <li>FAA JO 7110.10 — Flight Services</li>\n      <li>FAA JO 7340.2 — Contractions</li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><em>Note: Some documents have revision letters (e.g., \"-B,\" \"-C\") that change over time. Always use the latest edition on the FAA website or your EFB library.</em></p>\n\n    <h3 id=\"revisions\">Revisions Log</h3>\n    <p><em>Darcy Aviation Flight School, Policy and Procedures Manual — Revision History</em></p>\n    <table class=\"data-table\">\n      <thead><tr><th>Revision Number</th><th>Date</th><th>Section Affected</th><th>Description of Change</th><th>Approved By</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td class=\"id\">1.0</td><td>10/15/2025</td><td>-</td><td>Initial Release of Manual</td><td>BD</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"id\">1.1</td><td>11/25/2025</td><td>Safety Procedures &amp; Practices</td><td>Staff, Weather General, Wind Limits</td><td>BD</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"id\">1.2</td><td>12/29/2025</td><td>Added Section, Procedures</td><td>Winter Ops Section, Staff, Rwy Braking Restriction, Dispatching Procedure, Incident &amp; Accident Section update</td><td>BD</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"id\">1.3</td><td>01/01/26</td><td>Manual Title</td><td>Flight School Policy &amp; Procedures changed to Standard Operating Procedures</td><td>BD</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>",
